properties.areaDesc: Santa Barbara County South Coast; Santa Barbara County Mountains
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 1 at 3:56PM PST until February 3 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest to north winds 30 to 45 mph with damaging wind
gusts to 70 mph. Isolated gusts to 80 mph possible in the
foothills of the Santa Ynez range.

* WHERE...Santa Barbara County South Coast and Santa Barbara
County Mountains.

* WHEN...From 2 PM Sunday to noon PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down large objects such as
trees and power lines. Power outages are likely. High profile
vehicles, including big rigs could be blown over by the
powerful winds.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strongest winds Sunday night across the
Santa Ynez range and Santa Barbara south coast. Major roadways
that could be impacted by the powerful winds and wind damage
include Highways 101, 154, and 192.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Avoid travel if
possible during the height of the windstorm, and remember to check
the latest road reports if you must travel.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 2 PM SUNDAY TO NOON PST MONDAY
